Posterior predictive checks

True data plot

## Choice accuracy

# Preprocess data
df = output3$rawdata %>%
  group_by(subjID) %>%
  mutate(trial = row_number(),
         bin = cut(trial, breaks=10, labels=1:10),
         cond = factor(cond,
                       c(1, 2, 3)))

# Calculate accuracy per bin
df_mean = df %>%
  group_by(bin, cond) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(mean_correct = mean(choice == 1))
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'bin' (override with `.groups` argument)
# Plot result
df_mean %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = bin, y = mean_correct, 
             group = cond, fill = cond, 
             color = cond, shape = cond)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line() +
  ylab('Proportion choice optimal') +
  ylim(c(0.2, 1.0)) +
  ggtitle('True data') +
  theme_bw()

## RT
df_RT = output3$rawdata %>%
  mutate(cond = factor(cond,
                       c(1, 2, 3)),
         RT = ifelse(choice == 1, RT, -RT))

df_RT %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = RT)) +
  facet_wrap(~cond) +
  geom_density() +
  ggtitle('True data') +
  theme_bw()

One-step method

## Choice accuracy

# Calculate mean choice accuracy for each trial
data_os = output3$parVals$choice_os
data_os = ifelse(data_os == -1, NA,              # -1 to NA
                     ifelse(data_os == 1, 1, 0)) # (1, 2) to (1, 0)
data_os = apply(data_os, c(2, 3), mean)

# Transform into a data.frame
df_os   = melt(data_os) %>%
  dplyr::rename(subjID = Var1,
                trial = Var2,
                mean_correct = value)

# Integrate condition information
df_os = merge(df_os, 
              df[,c('subjID', 'trial', 'cond')], 
              all = TRUE) %>%
  arrange(subjID, trial)

# Split trials into bins
df_os = df_os %>%
  drop_na(cond) %>%
  group_by(subjID) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(bin = cut(trial, breaks=10, labels=1:10))

# Calculate accuracy for each bin
df_mean_os = df_os %>%
  drop_na(cond) %>%
  group_by(bin, cond) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(mean_correct = mean(mean_correct))
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'bin' (override with `.groups` argument)
# Plot
df_mean_os %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = bin, y = mean_correct, 
             group = cond, fill = cond, 
             color = cond, shape = cond)) +
  # scale_shape_manual(values = c("AB" = 2, "CD" = 1, "EF" = 0)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line() +
  ylab('Proportion choice optimal') +
  ylim(c(0.2, 1.0)) +
  ggtitle('Posterior prediction (one-step method)') +
  theme_bw()

## RT

numSims = dim(output3$parVals$mu_a)        # number of simulations
numSubjs = dim(output3$allIndPars)[1]      # number of subjects
maxT = max(table(output3$rawdata$subjID))  # maximum number of trials
cond = array(NA, c(numSims, numSubjs, maxT))
for (i in 1:numSubjs) {
  for (j in 1:maxT) {
    cond[, i, j] = as.integer(df[(df$subjID == i) & (df$trial == j), 'cond'])
  }
}

# Calculate mean choice accuracy for each trial
data_os = output3$parVals$RT_os
choice_os = output3$parVals$choice_os
data_os = ifelse(data_os == -1, NA, data_os)
data_os = ifelse(choice_os == 1, data_os, -data_os)

# Transform into a data.frame
df_os   = melt(data_os) %>%
  dplyr::rename(subjID = Var2,
                trial = Var3,
                RT = value)

# Integrate condition information
cond_vec = cond
dim(cond_vec) = numSims * numSubjs * maxT
df_os$cond = factor(cond_vec, c(1, 2, 3))

# Plot
df_os %>%
  filter(!is.na(cond)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = RT)) +
  facet_wrap(~cond) +
  geom_density() +
  xlim(c(-6, 6)) +
  ggtitle('Posterior prediction (one-step method)') +
  theme_bw()
